atom: Osama bin Laden was born on March 10, 1957.
Osama bin Laden was born in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia.
Osama bin Laden was born into a wealthy family.
Osama bin Laden's family owned a multinational construction business.
He was the 17th of 52 children of Mohammed bin Laden.
Mohammed bin Laden was a self-made billionaire.
Mohammed bin Laden immigrated from Yemen as a laborer.
Mohammed bin Laden rose to direct major construction projects.
The construction projects were for the Saudi royal family.
Bin Laden received a religiously focused education.
Bin Laden's education included Arabic literature.
Bin Laden's education included mathematics.
He attended King Abdulaziz University.
King Abdulaziz University is in Jeddah.
He studied economics.
He studied business administration.
He spent time at a university.
He was exposed to radical Islamic teachings.
His exposure to radical Islamic teachings occurred during his time at university.
The Soviet Union invaded Afghanistan in 1979.
Bin Laden joined the Afghan resistance, known as the mujahideen.
Bin Laden saw the Soviet Union's invasion of Afghanistan as an act of aggression against Islam.
He had wealth and connections.
He used his wealth and connections to fund the mujahideen.
He later formed the militant organization al-Qaeda.
Al-Qaeda was formed in 1988.
The Soviets withdrew from Afghanistan in 1989.
Bin Laden returned to Saudi Arabia.
Bin Laden's return to Saudi Arabia happened after the Soviet withdrawal from Afghanistan.
He criticized the Saudi monarchy.
His criticism led to his exile.
He was exiled to Sudan.
His exile happened in 1992.
He was in Sudan.
He continued to orchestrate violent acts.
The violent acts were against Western targets.
Sudan expelled bin Laden in 1996.
The expulsion of bin Laden from Sudan occurred under international pressure.
Bin Laden returned to Afghanistan after being expelled from Sudan.
Bin Laden received protection from the Taliban in Afghanistan.
Bin Laden is infamous.
Bin Laden orchestrated the September 11, 2001, terrorist attacks on the United States.
The September 11, 2001, terrorist attacks on the United States killed nearly 3,000 people.
There were attacks that preceded the U.S. launching a war in Afghanistan.
The U.S. launched a war in Afghanistan.
The U.S. aimed to capture bin Laden during the war in Afghanistan.
There was a nearly decade-long manhunt for bin Laden.
Bin Laden was killed by U.S. Navy SEALs.
The killing of bin Laden occurred in a raid.
The raid took place on his compound in Abbottabad, Pakistan.
The raid happened on May 2, 2011.
The man died.
His death marked the end of one of the most extensive manhunts in history.
His death dealt a significant blow to al-Qaeda.
